news.title: Colonies' information on Ludhiana civic body website hits font hurdle
news.para: ​Some of the information is in Punjabi fonts which are not readable for the devices that do not have those fonts. An RTI activist claimed that officials did this intentionally, so that actual information does not reach the masses.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Corporation identifies 700 defaulters owing tax dues above Rs 1 lakh
news.para: In the past two months, the corporation managed to collect around Rs 17 crore following the updation of tax database in all the wards.

news.title: Delhi model suggested for need-based changes in Chandigarh housing board
news.para: All the parties in attendance suggested that the Delhi need based changes pattern be taken as reference to regularisation of need based changes in CHB flats.

news.title: Mall owners likely to offer relief to retail stores, food outlets, multiplexes: SCAI
news.para: SCAI director Abhishek Bansal said some of the retailers have started approaching the property owners, raising their concerns over the impact on their business after the restrictions imposed by local authorities after a sudden surge in the pandemic cases.

news.title: Mumbai: Homebuyer fails to get possession, given Rs 2 crore
news.para: MahaRERA member Vijay Satbir Singh observed that the said MOU clearly provides that the home buyer agreed to purchase the said flat and the respondent agreed to sell the said flat to the complainant.

news.title: Several high-value property transactions in Delhi put on hold
news.para: "The government should build a mechanism as many elderly people are not able to register their will. Since a registered will is more authentic and acceptable, the testator prefers registering his will,” said Sunil Tyagi, managing partner of Zeus Law Associates.

news.title: Amazon in talks to lease space at DLF's new project in Gurgaon
news.para: During its Q2 analysts call in October, DLF had said it will soon start construction work on 2 million sq ft of office space in Gurgaon as it sees rising demand for grade A office buildings in the coming year.

news.title: Bombay HC rejects pre-arrest bail plea of four builders in cheating case
news.para: The HC single judge bench of Justice S V Kotwal had on January 11 turned down applications filed by S G Kallan, Abdul Zoeb and Raychel D’Souza in 2020, and a separate one filed by A R Tinani last year.

news.title: Brilloca to acquire building products manufacturing business of HSIL for Rs 630 crore
news.para: ​​Currently engaged in marketing and distribution of building products such as sanitaryware, faucets, plastic pipes and fittings, Brilloca said after the acquisition it will be backward integrated and have better control over the entire value chain, from manufacturing to after-sales.

news.title: Varanasi civic body freezes bank accounts of house tax debtors
news.para: VMCs zonal officer (trans-Varuna) PK Dwivedi said that despite issuance of demand notice and warrant many big debtors did not realized the need to clear their house tax.

news.title: Mumbai: In redevelopment market, future of heritage houses on fragile ground
news.para: Over the past two decades, several heritage properties have been redeveloped with their heritage facade retained and a tower built behind it.

news.title: Bengaluru: Govinda Reddy Layout citizens are in despair
news.para: At Govinda Reddy Layout (Ward no 50), near Hosa Road, local residents allege that the storm-water drains have been constructed at a higher level than their houses, which was not helping with the flooding at all.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body all set to notify construction & demolition waste policy
news.para: Since the C&D waste policy is a new one, it will be notified by the Punjab governor and UT administrator in consultation with senior officials of the Chandigarh administration.

news.title: Dip into e-wallet to pay property tax in Kolkata
news.para: ​​This apart, the KMC brass will also offer a citizen to apply for mutation of his/her properties online and upload the property-related documents for verification by the civic officials before issuing a mutation certificate.

news.title: Jharkhand: Brick kilns want exemption from green norms
news.para: ​​The brick manufacturers, who are ready to opt for cleaner technology, are sceptical that stringent laws may push the small and medium business owners out of the trade.
